# Toronto Rising — development style

This project is iterated **quickly**; requirements and layout change often.

## Prefer a minimal, current codebase

- **Do not** keep unused functions, dead branches, “just in case” placeholders, or obsolete compatibility shims unless the user explicitly asks to preserve them.
- **Do not** assume backward compatibility is required. When something is replaced or no longer referenced, **remove** it and update docs/comments that still describe the old behavior.
- When touching an area, **delete** clearly orphaned code paths rather than leaving commented-out or parallel “legacy” copies.
- After removals, **grep** for stale names (roles, tags, helpers) and fix **call sites, prints, and `.dev` docs** that still mention them.
- **Documentation:** When behavior, paths, or APIs change, **update `.dev/` and `docs/solutions/` in the same change** — do not wait for the user to ask. See **Documentation Updates — ABSOLUTE REQUIREMENT** in `.cursorrules`.
- **Linear tracking:** Keep Linear, [RUNNING TASKLIST](../../.dev/RUNNING%20TASKLIST.md), and code aligned on every task — see `.cursor/rules/toronto-rising-linear.mdc`. Linear sync is part of done, not a follow-up. Quick capture before scheduling: [INBOX.md](../../.dev/INBOX.md).
- When adding/changing conditions, read [Conditions System Guide](../../.dev/PC%20Data%20&%20Tracking/Conditions%20System%20Guide.md) (Agent quick guide) before editing the registry or consumers.
- For synchronization flow and naming conventions, follow `.cursor/rules/toronto-rising-synchronization.mdc`.
- **Lua local function order (top recurring runtime bug):** In each file/chunk, define `local function` helpers **before** any caller (`Global.*`, `HUD_*`, `onObject*`, other locals), or forward-declare (`local foo` at top, `foo = function` later). Late locals are invisible to earlier functions → **`attempt to call a nil value`**; build does not catch it. **Before finishing any Lua task:** grep new helper names vs caller line numbers. See [`.cursor/rules/toronto-rising-lua-local-function-order.mdc`](../../.cursor/rules/toronto-rising-lua-local-function-order.mdc) and [`docs/solutions/lua-local-function-order.md`](../../docs/solutions/lua-local-function-order.md). **Do not append new `local function` at file bottom** without checking all callers above.
- Give proactive pushback when a requested path is unsound or overly complex; explain the risk and propose a simpler architecture-aligned alternative immediately.
- Favor single-authority ownership per subsystem and call out dual-writer/dual-source-of-truth designs before implementing them.

Agents should default to: **only what is current and actually exercised** stays in the tree.
